        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 4:36AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 436 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 2 miles northeast of Stidham to 5 miles northeast
of Kinta. Movement was northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Kanima...                         Greenleaf State Park...
Whitefield...                     Oktaha...
Summit...                         Webbers Falls...
Kinta...                          Porum...
Warner...                         Stigler...
Checotah...                       Lake Eufaula State Park...
Gore...                           Keefeton...
Lequire...                        Gans...
Sallisaw...                       Rentiesville...
Briartown...                      Vian...

This includes Interstate 40 in Oklahoma between mile markers 258 and
315.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 AM CDT for
southeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
